Kano state governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has extended the tenure of the State Head of Service, Dr Kabiru Shehu, as Acting Head of Service. The extension of tenure for Dr Kabiru Shehu was announced a day after his service as Head of service elapsed. A press statement by Abba Anwar, Chief Press Secretary to the Governor of Kano State quoted his boss to have said that “Dr Shehu would continue as Acting, till when a substantive Head of Service is appointed. ” The statement noted that “Dr. Shehu has started infusing more blood to the life of the state public service. Adding that, “Dr. Kabiru Shehu has equally come up with more strategies in strengthening relationships between government and workers.” Ganduje, therefore, urged “public servants to continue relating well with him, as when he was first appointed as the State Head of Service.”